text: Pushepatapa Creek is a stream in the U.S. state of Louisiana. Pushepatapa is a name most likely derived from the Choctaw language; it's purported to mean "sandy bottom". Variant names are "Poosheepatapa Creek", "Poosheepatopa Creek", "Pushapatappa Creek", "Pushepetapa Creek", "Pushepetappy Creek", and "Pushpetappy Creek". ==References== Category:Rivers of Louisiana Category:Bodies of water of Washington Parish, Louisiana
title: Pushepatapa Creek
